&lt;h2&gt;IN A NUTSHELL…&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;ve spent over a decade building a brand people genuinely love, through our products, our presence online, and the way we show up in the world. Now we&#39;re showing up in person. Our first U.S. store has opened in New York&#39;s Flatiron District, and it won&#39;t be our last. But a great store doesn&#39;t run itself. Someone needs to manage the build-outs, lead the Store Managers, and stitch together the systems that make it all hold together. That&#39;s where you come in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Area Manager will be the person behind the scenes making Bellroy&#39;s U.S. retail presence real. While Store Managers focus on the customer experience, you&#39;ll be focused on everything that makes that experience possible: While our Retail Steering team and senior leadership sort out the real estate, including site selection and lease negotiations, you&#39;ll own fitouts and how our stores actually operate when they open. Leading the team that runs them, and writing the operational playbook that lets us do it well, and then do it again.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;ve ever wanted to build a retail operation rather than inherit one, and you care about doing it at a company that actually walks the walk, we&#39;re a Certified B Corporation™, and we&#39;d love to talk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who gets energised by firsts, finds satisfaction in the operational detail, and wants to help us prove that retail can be done differently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;YOU COULD BE THE ONE IF YOU HAVE…&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Three to five years in multi-site or store leadership, accountable for sales, team, and customer experience. You might be stepping up from an area, district, cluster, or store manager role, or have recently moved into a head-office retail position.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of leading and developing frontline managers and teams. You set clear expectations, coach people, give direct feedback, and hold the standard without making it miserable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort owning retail performance. You can read the numbers, spot what&#39;s slipping early, and do something about it before the month closes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An eye for the operational detail that keeps a store humming: rosters that work, stock that&#39;s where it should be, visual standards that hold, and opening and closing rhythms that don&#39;t wobble.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Built or embedded repeatable processes before, and documented them well enough that the next person could pick them up and run.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The kind of temperament that&#39;s energised by firsts. This is still early days for US retail, so there&#39;s no finished playbook waiting for you. You&#39;ll help write it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A habit of staying close to what good retail looks like, what competitors are doing and where the interesting ideas are, and you bring that thinking back to the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Even if your background doesn&#39;t tick every box, if you&#39;ve run a great store or team and you&#39;re energised by helping build something from the early days, we&#39;d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;IN YOUR FIRST FEW MONTHS, YOU&#39;D LIKELY…&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help coordinate the Flatiron build-out and work side by side with the Store Manager to get our first US store open and running well, from daily operational standards through to the experience customers have on the floor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare for a potential second U.S. store opening by December, we&#39;re currently in lease/legal review for a second location, so there&#39;s a real chance you&#39;ll be supporting two store openings before the end of the year.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Connect regularly with our retail team in Australia to borrow what&#39;s already working and adapt it for the US.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach and develop the store team, setting the bar for how Bellr

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IN A NUTSHELL...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is Bellroy&#39;s first store in Melbourne, the city the brand calls home and we&#39;re building it to be something &lt;em&gt;genuinely&lt;/em&gt; good. The retail team&#39;s job is to bring the Bellroy experience to life in person: thoughtful, knowledgeable and a little unexpected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Assistant Store Manager, you&#39;re the person the Store Manager hands the reins to with confidence. You know the numbers and the floor in equal measure. You can navigate a complex customer situation with the same ease you bring to a morning huddle, and you&#39;re the kind of presence that lifts a team (without making it obvious you&#39;re doing it). Ownership isn&#39;t just a word here, you&#39;ll be shaping how this store operates from the ground up, feeding ideas and observations upward in a way that actually influences decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bellroy is a Certified B Corporation™, which means the way we do business is part of the product. Sustainability, materials, responsible supply chain; these aren&#39;t footnotes, they&#39;re things you&#39;ll speak to every day, fluently and genuinely. You&#39;ll be close to the people making decisions, on a team where good thinking is welcomed regardless of where it comes from.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;People who&#39;ve worked in retail and genuinely love it often say the same thing: they want autonomy without being abandoned, accountability without being micro-managed, and a product they can actually stand behind. That&#39;s what this role offers. Bellroy is a considered brand and this store will reflect that, which means you&#39;ll have the space to do the job properly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU COULD BE THE ONE IF YOU HAVE …&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years retail supervisory experience and the instincts to match - you can read a floor, spot a pattern in the numbers, and respond with intention rather than reaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A real way with customers, especially in complex moments. Escalated complaints, warranty queries, and considered purchase decisions all get the same thoughtful attention as a first hello&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to train and support others without making it feel like training. You share knowledge naturally and people feel more confident after talking to you&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine interest in the product. You don&#39;t need to be a gear obsessive, but you should enjoy going deep on what makes something well-made and worth owning, and communicating that in a way that feels natural&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience running the operational side of a store: stock processes, cash handling, deliveries, and the daily discipline that keeps everything else working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort with ambiguity and early-stage problems. This store is still finding its feet, which means some things won&#39;t have a playbook yet, and that energises you rather than frustrating you&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A settled, grounded energy on the floor - the kind that steadies the team on a hard day, without anyone quite knowing how.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Even if you don&#39;t tick every box, if you&#39;re drawn to the challenge of helping build something from scratch in a brand you genuinely respect, we&#39;d love to hear from you!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU WERE HERE LAST WEEK, YOU MIGHT HAVE …&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the morning huddle, briefed the team on the week&#39;s priorities and a new product update, and walked out of it feeling like everyone was actually ready&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stepped in on a warranty situation that had gotten complicated, resolved it calmly, and fed back to the Store Manager what you&#39;d noticed about how similar queries were landing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewed the week&#39;s performance numbers, spotted that one product category was underperfor

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IN A NUTSHELL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bellroy is on a mission to build a meaningful presence in China and we’re just getting started. Over the past four years, we’ve shifted from cross-border selling to a fully localised operation. As campaign complexity grows and the ecommerce landscape evolves, we&#39;re looking for a Channel Manager who can bring real depth to marketplace management, not just coverage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be responsible for shaping Bellroy’s ecommerce channel strategy and translating it into clear commercial and operational plans. Working closely with our TP partners and external agencies, you’ll set priorities, provide direction, and ensure campaigns and day-to-day operations are executed efficiently and to a high standard. You’ll use data and insights to identify opportunities, optimise performance, and continuously improve how we show up across key marketplaces, while elevating the consumer experience and ensuring a consistent, premium brand journey across all touchpoints. Inside Bellroy you&#39;ll sit alongside the broader Operations team and have a direct line to our Country Manager, so when you spot something worth doing, you won&#39;t be shouting into a void. Good thinking gets heard here, and the person who did the work gets the credit for it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plenty of people in marketplace roles spend their days squeezed between an agency on one side and internal sign-offs on the other, never quite holding the wheel. This role hands you the wheel. You get genuine ownership of the channel, the room to back your own analysis, and a clear path to grow as the China business does.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;YOU COULD BE THE ONE IF YOU HAVE…&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Three or more years running e-commerce, marketplace or digital commerce, with real hands-on time on platforms like Tmall, JD or Douyin. You know how these channels behave, not just in theory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of managing external agencies or TPs. You can brief them well, tell good work from filler, and step in when something&#39;s off.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuinely analytical head. You&#39;re comfortable living in the numbers across sales, traffic, conversion, ROI and profitability, and you use them to decide what to do next, not just to report what already happened.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The instinct to take something and run with it. You can hold channel performance and daily operations on your own without waiting to be told the next step.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A continuous-improvement streak. You notice when a process is clunky and you fix it, rather than working around it for the third month running.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to turn what the data is telling you into a commercial plan someone can actually act on.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curiosity about new tools, including where AI and automation can take the dull parts off your plate, and the appetite to keep learning as the platforms change under your feet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A real interest in consumer brands and where digital commerce is heading. The people who do well here actually care about this stuff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Even if you don&#39;t tick every box, if the idea of taking full ownership of Bellroy&#39;s China marketplaces excites you, we&#39;d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
