&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Noticed conversion slipping on a key Tmall product page, dug into the data to work out why, and rewritten the listing to fix it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sat down with our TP agency to brief them on the next big campaign and pushed back where the plan wasn&#39;t sharp enough.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pulled the week&#39;s performance together for Country Manager and the Operations team, and flagged the one number that needed a decision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconciled sales reporting and tidied the dashboard so next week&#39;s read is

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IN A NUTSHELL…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bellroy has spent 15 years building products that simplify the carry experience and a customer base that keeps coming back for more. Our CRM program is a big part of why. It&#39;s how we stay in touch with customers in ways that feel relevant, considered, and worth their attention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an CRM Lead to own and drive that program. You&#39;ll be responsible for our email and lifecycle marketing - the flows, the campaigns, the segmentation, the testing, the reporting, and the constant work of making it all better. You&#39;ll work closely with your manager to shape the direction of the program, and then you&#39;ll make it happen; building out the plans, executing and using data to keep pushing things forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re someone who&#39;s spent a few years getting deep into CRM and lifecycle marketing, who&#39;s comfortable owning performance metrics, and who gets energy from building something that works and then making it better, keep reading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU COULD BE THE ONE IF YOU…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have 4-6 years of hands-on CRM or lifecycle marketing experience, ideally in ecommerce, retail, or direct-to-consumer brands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Know how to build, manage, and optimise email flows and campaigns; not just execute them, but assess whether they&#39;re working and figure out what to do next&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand customer segmentation, lifecycle stages, and how to best use data to drive personalisation and retention&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have worked with email platforms and customer data tools (Klaviyo, Braze, SFMC, Segment, or similar - we care more about your process knowledge than which specific platform/s you&#39;ve worked in)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are comfortable owning CRM performance metrics: email revenue, retention rates, flow conversion, list health etc. and can talk about what you&#39;ve improved and how&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience with (or strong interest in) SMS as a channel, and can think about how to introduce it thoughtfully alongside emails&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience working cross-functionally with creative, data, and tech teams; briefing clearly, following up well, and keeping things moving without needing to be chased&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a detail-oriented, process-driven working style but can step back and see the bigger picture when it matters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are proactive - you see a gap or an opportunity and you raise it, rather than waiting for someone to point it out.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU WERE HERE LAST WEEK, HERE’S SOME THINGS YOU MIGHT HAVE DONE…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewed performance across our automated flows - identified a post-purchase sequence that was underperforming, and put together a plan to rebuild it with updated logic, timing, and content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Built audience segments for an upcoming campaign, set up A/B tests on subject lines and send times, and QA&#39;d everything before it went live&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Worked with our marketing analyst to define new customer traits for more personalised targeting across email, ads, and our website&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Done a deep dive into our RFM segments, identified a group of lapsed customers worth reactivating, and developed a targeted win-back campaign to bring them back&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scoped out what an SMS program could look like for Bellroy - researching platforms, mapping use cases, and thinking through how to maintain our brand voice in a new channel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pulled together a monthly CRM performance report, not just the numbers, but what they mean, what&#39;s working, and where the next opportunities are&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Worked with the creative team to plan next month

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IN A NUTSHELL…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a People Development Lead to help our people grow as deliberately as our headcount has. You&#39;ll sit in our People &amp;amp; Culture team, report to our Chief People Officer, and help drive the programmes, rituals and bodies of work that help our crew - wherever they&#39;re based - learn, grow and do their best work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Over the past few years Bellroy has grown its global workforce, and we&#39;ve put real care into our learning culture and how we handle performance and engagement. We&#39;re proud of what we&#39;ve built, and here&#39;s plenty more to do for someone who loves doing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Development at Bellroy is broader than training. Training teaches someone to run a new procedure while development grows the person underneath it, we care a lot about the second. We want someone with a real point of view on how people grow, including the models and the psychology behind it and who can turn that thinking into practice. You&#39;ll build onboarding that sets new starters up well, develop managers who can have the conversations that matter, and coach crew through the tricky moments. You&#39;ll shape how all of this works and, just as often, be the person making it happen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AI is changing how our crew works, too. You&#39;ll help build the frameworks that guide how people use it in their roles, shape how it shows up in our culture (including how new starters meet it in onboarding), and experiment with tools that give managers direct support day to day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a seriously considered environment, products designed with intention, a Certified B Corporation™ to business as a force for good, and a crew who genuinely love learning and improving. Decision making sits close to the work, we&#39;re honest about what&#39;s working and what&#39;s not, and we care about doing things properly rather than ticking boxes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU COULD BE THE ONE IF YOU...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Around 5+ years spent growing people and capability. That might be in people development, organisational development or HR business partnering, or somewhere less obvious, like Big 4 or strategy consulting or professional services (we care more about the development work you&#39;ve done than the function you did it in)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run workshops or training sessions that changed how people worked afterwards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coached or supported managers through tricky performance and people conversations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong coordination and organisation. You keep a lot of moving parts on track, hit the dates you commit to, and people trust that what you&#39;ve picked up will get done&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A considered point of view on how people develop that goes deeper than how they&#39;re trained. You draw on real models of how humans learn, grow and behave at work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort with engagement and performance data (survey tools, dashboards, spreadsheets) and a knack for turning numbers into clear, human insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands on experience with AI. You&#39;re curious and have experimented with these tools in your own work, you notice how the people around you use them, and you can write guidance people follow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A warm, candid style. You can have honest conversations without drama, and you&#39;re as happy listening as advising&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus points if you&#39;ve worked with frontline or retail teams. We&#39;re building out our retail presence and value someone who understands how capability grows in fast-paced, customer-facing environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you don&#39;t tick every box but you&#39;re excited about building a strong development culture at Bellroy, we&#39;d still like to hear from you.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
