&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IN A NUTSHELL…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since we launched with a range of six wallets 16+ years ago, we now release about 50 new products a year (give or take) and our Production team is key to getting all of these products (and those yet to come) out into the world! We’re on the search for someone to support them to get our products into the hands of our customers reliably, and with impeccable quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you&#39;ll quality-check our product samples, provide feedback to our manufacturers, and manage our product archive based in the office. You&#39;ll also handle transactional processing and organise deliveries from our HQ to our warehouses and partners. You&#39;ll be supporting our production team with administrative duties and working closely with our photography and wholesale teams to make sure they have the product samples they need on time. There&#39;s a lot to keep track of, so you will need to be organised, logical and effective in your approach with the ability to make a plan and stick to it, ticking off your to-do list methodically.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You might not have direct experience in product quality, but if you&#39;ve worked in customer service, retail, warehouse operations or any role that&#39;s taught you to juggle multiple tasks, notice details others miss, and manage logistics or team workflows, you’ll have transferable skills we value. What matters most is that you&#39;re keen to learn and develop your expertise in a production environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bring us your effective organisational skills and hunger to learn, in return, we&#39;ll offer the tools for you to do your thing, a world-class crew to learn from, and the support you need to flourish.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU COULD BE THE ONE, IF YOU...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Want to develop your career in a quality control, production space (or might have some experience in this space already)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have strong organisation skills, a sharp eye for detail and love a good spreadsheet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are reliable and methodical with logistics, data entry and keeping records accurate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoy working with your hands and getting a feel for the products you are assessing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess excellent communication and relationship management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can pick up potential issues or inconsistencies before they become a problem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have an uncanny ability to understand the needs of those around you&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Want to work collaboratively in a team within a fast-paced, agile environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working with computers, general office software, and printers - no advanced experience required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU WERE HERE LAST WEEK, HERE ARE SOME OF THE THINGS YOU MIGHT HAVE DONE...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality checked product that arrived at HQ and prepared feedback for our suppliers for the pieces that didn’t meet our standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Received incoming shipments into HQ, recorded them in our systems and sent packages out to our suppliers and partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Created, proofed and distributed barcodes for new products and got them to our suppliers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spoken with our photography and wholesale team to understand what samples you need to procure for them and when&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Kept our product archive and sample stock organised, accurate, and easy to find&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Instructed our warehouse teams how to inspect a new batch of products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Noticed an important delivery stuck in customs and found out what was needed to release it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organised new products to be sent out from our HQ to the warehouse and followed up with our warehouse te

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IN A NUTSHELL…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since we launched with six wallets over 15 years ago, we now release around 50 new products a year, and the complexity of getting those products right has grown with us. Our Production team is at the heart of that work, and we&#39;re looking for a Quality Assurance Lead who sweats the details, so our customers never have to.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to our Production and Quality Assurance Manager, you&#39;ll own our quality control and assurance process end-to-end. You&#39;ll contribute to building and maintaining the quality frameworks that underpin how we work — owning defined areas of the process independently, and helping calibrate how we make quality decisions across the business. That also means being the main point of contact for all supplier quality matters, overseeing inspections from pre-production through to pre-shipment release, managing NCRs and corrective action plans through to resolution, and coordinating third-party inspections. You&#39;ll oversee factory quality staff and remote QA at overseas manufacturer sites, manage quality processes and documentation within our system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn&#39;t a flag-and-move-on role. You&#39;ll dig into the production &amp;amp; quality handbook, supplier data and factory processes, getting to the bottom of issues, not just the surface of them. You&#39;ll track quality KPIs, identify trends, and bring forward improvement proposals. You&#39;ll also have real input into building and maintaining the quality management systems that underpin everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you bring a sharp eye for detail, solid technical grounding in quality assurance, experience leading supplier relationships, and a genuine itch for continuous improvement - we&#39;d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU COULD BE THE ONE IF YOU HAVE…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in a quality control or quality assurance role, ideally in soft goods, accessories; with a track record of managing quality across multiple concurrent product lines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with overseas manufacturers and managing remote QA staff on-site, including maintaining quality standards across different time zones and working environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with pre-production and bulk sample approval processes, including interpreting and applying QC manuals, spec sheets, and construction standards to assess conformance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A solid technical understanding of quality control methodologies (e.g. AQL sampling, NCR management, root cause analysis, corrective action processes), relevant industry standards, and how they apply across different manufacturing environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience producing quality reporting, including identifying cross-category trends and translating data into clear recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing supplier quality relationships directly, conducting or coordinating supplier quality audits, managing non-conformance reports, and driving corrective actions through to resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with quality management systems, including maintaining accurate quality documentation and data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience coordinating or overseeing third-party inspections and pre-shipment quality releases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong skills in Excel or Google Sheets, including the ability to track KPIs, analyse quality metrics, and present findings clearly to both technical and non-technical stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading or mentoring others, with the ability to delegate effectively and develop capability in a small team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional attention to detail and time management; able to juggle multiple inspections, deadlines and supplier conversations without things slipping&lt;/li&gt;
